 Just a parenthetical remark: an Emacs user would find this exchange about
 three choices somewhat bewildering.  In Emacs, it would be obvious that the
 way to implement this is with a message in the minibuffer: "Insert/Overwrite
 toggle turned off, <action> to turn it on".  That way, if someone *really*
 wanted it, they would hit Insert a few times and eventually see the message
 (assuming they missed it the first time) and then know what to do.
 
