 On Sat, Dec 20, 2008 at 5:18 PM, John Clements
 <clements@brinckerhoff.org> wrote:
 > In my opinion, the pop-up is preferable to the menu entry. My guess is that
 > there are currently 0 people in the world who switch between insert &
 > overwrite mode in DrScheme more than once every five minutes.
 
 This seems to be a common opinion at this point. I suspect that there
 are people who like to toggle modes, but that is also doable with a
 dialog box (ie having a check box in the dialog box that avoids the
 dialog box in the future.
 
 Still, it was easier to just add a preference, and I think we've
 probably talked this to death by now. So I added the preference
 (defaults to disabled). This means that no one will trip over
 overwrite mode accidentally now. You must first enable it before you
 can trip over it. Hopefully we won't get too many complaints about
 'missing overwrite mode' or else I'll have to go with the dialog.
 
 Ride me to the glue factory, horse!
 
 Robby
