 Probably I should get to that someday. For now, the modeline in
 DrScheme, as I'm sure you're aware, since I've mentioned it many times
 before, has 10 or so fixed things that can currently even all appear
 at once, so there isn't really space for more stuff. There is, of
 course, a way to make additional lines at the bottom, but I'm sure you
 or someone else would complain that they take up too much space were I
 to use them (in this case anyway).
 
 Regardless of all that, I still think that a dialog box with some kind
 of "don't ask me again" check box is more appropriate that a question
 that would be asked in the minibuffer in Emacs for this particular
 interaction with the user. It also happens to more in keeping with
 modern GUI norms.
 
